    {
        "text": "Number One: Achilles and the Tortoise.",
        "startTime": 6175,
        "endTime": 8453,
        "slowStartTime": 9413,
        "slowEndTime": 12904
    },
    {
        "text": "How could a humble tortoise beat the legendary Greek hero Achilles in a race?",
        "startTime": 9352,
        "endTime": 13124,
        "slowStartTime": 14178,
        "slowEndTime": 19911
    },
    {
        "text": "The Greek philosopher Xeno liked the challenge and came up with this paradox.",
        "startTime": 13779,
        "endTime": 17151,
        "slowStartTime": 20819,
        "slowEndTime": 25952
    },
    {
        "text": "First, the tortoise is given a slight head start.",
        "startTime": 17747,
        "endTime": 20086,
        "slowStartTime": 26770,
        "slowEndTime": 30354
    },
    {
        "text": "Anyone fancying a flutter would still rush to put their money on Achilles.",
        "startTime": 20909,
        "endTime": 23953,
        "slowStartTime": 31514,
        "slowEndTime": 36154
    },
    {
        "text": "But Xeno pointed out that to overtake him,...",
        "startTime": 24351,
        "endTime": 26399,
        "slowStartTime": 36676,
        "slowEndTime": 39823
    },
    {
        "text": "...Achilles would first have to cover the distance...",
        "startTime": 26634,
        "endTime": 28451,
        "slowStartTime": 40101,
        "slowEndTime": 42901
    },
    {
        "text": "...to the point where the tortoise began.",
        "startTime": 28565,
        "endTime": 30012,
        "slowStartTime": 42998,
        "slowEndTime": 45243
    },
    {
        "text": "In that time, the tortoise would have moved...",
        "startTime": 30757,
        "endTime": 32291,
        "slowStartTime": 46285,
        "slowEndTime": 48662
    },
    {
        "text": "... so Achilles would have to cover that distance...",
        "startTime": 32668,
        "endTime": 34433,
        "slowStartTime": 49152,
        "slowEndTime": 51874
    },
    {
        "text": "...giving the tortoise time to amble forward a bit more.",
        "startTime": 34775,
        "endTime": 37015,
        "slowStartTime": 52312,
        "slowEndTime": 55748
    },
    {
        "text": "Logically, this would carry on forever.",
        "startTime": 37909,
        "endTime": 39549,
        "slowStartTime": 57014,
        "slowEndTime": 59549
    },
    {
        "text": "However small the gap between them,...",
        "startTime": 40114,
        "endTime": 41416,
        "slowStartTime": 60321,
        "slowEndTime": 62349
    },
    {
        "text": "...the tortoise would still be able to move forward while Achilles was catching up,...",
        "startTime": 41693,
        "endTime": 44945,
        "slowStartTime": 62690,
        "slowEndTime": 67643
    },
    {
        "text": "...meaning that Achilles could never overtake.",
        "startTime": 45567,
        "endTime": 47426,
        "slowStartTime": 68501,
        "slowEndTime": 71364
    },
    {
        "text": "Taken to an extreme, this bizarre paradox suggests that all movement is impossible.",
        "startTime": 48275,
        "endTime": 52798,
        "slowStartTime": 72563,
        "slowEndTime": 79422
    },
    {
        "text": "But it did lead to a realization...",
        "startTime": 53421,
        "endTime": 54938,
        "slowStartTime": 80281,
        "slowEndTime": 82632
    },
    {
        "text": "...that something finite can be divided an infinite number of times.",
        "startTime": 55009,
        "endTime": 58443,
        "slowStartTime": 82664,
        "slowEndTime": 87890
    },
    {
        "text": "This concept of an infinite series is used in finance to work out mortgage payments...",
        "startTime": 59473,
        "endTime": 63900,
        "slowStartTime": 89359,
        "slowEndTime": 96075
    },
    {
        "text": "...which is why they take an infinite amount of time to pay off.",
        "startTime": 64283,
        "endTime": 66679,
        "slowStartTime": 96575,
        "slowEndTime": 100243
    }
]